Quote:  The natives here [in Taranaki] are in fear of their old enemies the `Wicatus' coming, but it appears their visit is intended for a friendly one, or to  ringa-ring (shake hands). <i>Ibid.</i> t 68 They [Maoris] were very civil, indeed the habit of shaking hands with every one became at last disagreeable, for if you met them a dozen times a day the ringa-ring must not be omitted, ...
